name: Welcome Cat
description: Welcome cat or The Maneki-Neko (招き猫, lit. 'beckoning cat') is a common Japanese figurine that is often believed to bring good luck to the owner. In modern times, they are usually made of ceramic or plastic. The figurine depicts a cat, traditionally a calico Japanese Bobtail, with a paw raised in a Japanese beckoning gesture. The figurines are often displayed in shops, restaurants, pachinko parlors, dry cleaners, laundromats, bars, casinos, hotels, nightclubs, and other businesses, generally near the entrance. Some Maneki-Neko is equipped with a mechanical paw that slowly moves back and forth.
